summary: This is an email chain from September 2021 between a U.S. Attorney's Office prosecutor and a Customs and Border Protection (CBP) Task Force Officer, discussing a request for CBP travel records from the 1990s for an unnamed French female individual, to compare against the travel of Ghislaine Maxwell and Jeffrey Epstein. The correspondence highlights ongoing investigative efforts to establish travel timelines.

persons.name: Jared Eannucci
persons.context: Mentioned as having passed along contact information for a CBP Task Force Officer to an Assistant United States Attorney.

events.title: Request for 1990s CBP Records
events.description: An Assistant United States Attorney requests CBP travel records from the 1990s for an unnamed French female to compare against the travel of Ghislaine Maxwell and Jeffrey Epstein.

events.title: Initial Contact Regarding CBP Records
events.description: An Assistant United States Attorney makes initial contact with a CBP Task Force Officer, having been referred by Jared Eannucci, to discuss a question in one of their cases.

keyFacts: Investigators were seeking CBP travel records from the 1990s for an unnamed French female individual.
The purpose was to compare these travel dates against the travel of Ghislaine Maxwell and Jeffrey Epstein.
The email notes a data limitation: for the timeframe in question, CBP only recorded inbound arrivals, not outbound departures.
The communication is marked as Law Enforcement Sensitive/For Official Use Only, indicating the sensitive nature of the ongoing investigation.
